# Receptor cells & channel specificity


**Important concepts and terms:**
- Describe and elucidate the transduction of stimuli into electric signals with the help of an example.

**Transduction:** 
Transduction is the conversion of a sensory stimulus from one form to another.  A physical stimulus is converted into an action potential, which is transmitted along axons towards the central nervous system for integration (Integration is processing of information by the CNS). It is a step in the larger process of sensory processing.
